## Google Cloud Deployment (MVP 2.0)

To "clone" the app into Google and avoid Vercel lock-in, we will deploy to **Google Cloud Run**.

### Configuration
#### [NEW] [Dockerfile](file:///Users/georgegayl/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/instant-faq-generator/Dockerfile)
- Multi-stage build optimized for Next.js standalone output.

#### [NEW] [cloudbuild.yaml](file:///Users/georgegayl/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/instant-faq-generator/cloudbuild.yaml)
- CI/CD configuration for Google Cloud Build.

### Deployment Steps
1.  **Containerize**: Build the Docker image.
2.  **Push**: Upload to Google Artifact Registry.
3.  **Deploy**: Run on Cloud Run (serverless container platform).

> [!NOTE]
> Since `gcloud` CLI is not installed in this environment, you can deploy by pushing this code to a GitHub repository and connecting it to **Google Cloud Build**, or by installing the Google Cloud SDK locally.
